TPU90A Grippy Tire CAD published (Finally) FIRST
4336 did a redesign to try and minimize tread print time. We’re utilizing a 2 piece Onyx hub and a TPU90 filament tread. Print time on the tread is under 5 hours. NOT original tread pattern but extremely happy with wear and traction. At most, we would change treads after quals. Last set we put on for Elims at Bayou lasted at numerous drive practice meetings afterwards. Just changed them out yesterday. Will edit & upload a photo when back in shop. [tire1] [tire2]

We used completely different designs, but all Filament is not made the same. Trial N’ Terror has found that the Build Series TPU from Matterhackers has the ideal material properties for printing wheel tread. As some TPU will deform under the heat of driving.

But we never had to change the wheels due to failure or wear. We just changed them incase
